description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic Nurse/Paramedic Practitioner to join our CQC rated ‘Outstanding’ Trust, within our Urgent Treatment Centre (UTC) that is part of the Urgent Care Service for a 12 month fixed term contract covering Maternity leave.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Based at West Berkshire Community Hospital, the UTC is a modern environment serving the local population and within our wider Urgent Care Service in both Thatcham and Reading.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will find our small team to be progressive, committed and extremely friendly, where you will be jointly responsible for setting high standards of care. This role is ideal for Advanced Practitioners from many backgrounds including nursing and paramedic to join an already diverse and skilled team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Job&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will assess, treat and discharge patients who access the Urgent Care Service and document the care given&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Intervene appropriately to assist the patient with urgent health care needs and prioritise as required to give effective emergency care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate a high standard of clinical skills to include suturing, plastering, interpretation of x-rays, eye care, near patient testing and life support skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with patients in order to support compliance and adherence to prescribed treatments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide information and advice on prescribed and non-prescription medication, medication regimes, side effects and interactions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Some of the benefits of joining our team:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;AfC Salary ranging from &lt;strong&gt;£37,570 - £43.772&lt;/strong&gt; per annum&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working opportunities and a strong emphasis on your work, life balance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Annual leave – 27 days for new starters, plus bank holidays. Increasing to 29 days after 5 years and 33 days after 10 years NHS service. Pro rata for part time staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent learning and development opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary sacrifice scheme for a new car&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous maternity, paternity and adoption leave for eligible staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced IT enablement and support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confidential telephone care service providing independent support and advice for staff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;And so much more&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;4&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;“must haves” for you to be considered for this role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Register nurse or registered paramedic&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minor Injuries trained&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minor Illness experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in requesting and interpreting X-rays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you recognise yourself in these requirements, we would recommend you apply today!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are happy to answer any questions that you may have. Please don’t hesitate to call: Gemma Thomas on 01635 273508/ 07776226538 or email: gemma.thomas@berkshire.nhs.uk who’ll be delighted to help.&lt;/p&gt;
